Omg, watching those tests with m cars and it makes me mad. Cmon guys! I’m driving bmw and it takes literally 1 minute to read how to use a launch control in instruction which is actually digital and is in front of you in the cars computer!
It clearly says that the engine must me 1)hot enough(considering that’s done, despite the exhaust sound doesn’t sound like this)
2) provide gearbox at least 5min between launches to keep the temperature right for it for the optimal result.
3) hold the full throttle for 2-3 secs before launching to give time for the gearbox and engine to pair together and deliver optimal outcome. They hold it really not enough, it’s even seen from the position of the car before launch and you can hear that the sound engine delivers is not one you must hear before launching M5.

Guys, the way you launch them is definitely wrong, please, work on it.

I used to launch M5 and M5 comp dozens of times and it delivers brilliant result. It’s actually really good. Have never heard anything bad about launching it but hear!
